\ Word-local variables: | name ... | declaration, to assignment, bare-name read.
\ Covers single/multiple locals, nested-scope depth, shadowing, recursion,
\ and interaction with delimited continuations (shift/resume).

\ -- 1: single local, square via x*x
: sq | x | to x  x x * ;
5 sq . cr

\ -- 2: two locals, assignment order (to b to a binds in declaration order)
: hyp | a b | to b to a  a a * b b * + ;
3 4 hyp . cr

\ -- 3: nested quotation reads an outer local (depth path, no inner frame)
: nest | x | to x  [ 10 20 30 ] [: x + :] map ;
100 nest . cr

\ -- 4: inner quotation's own local shadows the outer one
: shadow | x | to x  [: | x | to x  x x * :] 9 swap execute  x + ;
4 shadow . cr

\ -- 5: recursion — each call gets its own frame
: fact | n | to n  n 1 lt if 1 else n  n 1 - fact * then ;
5 fact . cr

\ -- 6: a local set before shift is read after resume (frame relocation)
: shifter shift ;
: worker | x | to x  shifter  x * ;
: ex reset 7 worker ;
ex 3 swap resume . cr

\ -- 7: multi-shot — the same continuation resumed twice, local intact each time
ex dup  5 swap resume . cr
        6 swap resume . cr

\ -- 8: |> single local, receives from stack at the bar
: sq2 |> x | x x * ;
5 sq2 . cr

\ -- 9: |> two locals — slot order matches declaration (a, then b)
: hyp2 |> a b | a a * b b * + ;
3 4 hyp2 . cr

\ -- 10: |> three locals — verifies (a b c -- ...) order
: combo |> a b c | a 100 *  b 10 *  c  + + ;
1 2 3 combo . cr

\ -- 11: |> inside a recursion (own frame per call)
: fact2 |> n | n 1 lt if 1 else n  n 1 - fact2 * then ;
6 fact2 . cr

\ -- 12: |> outer local visible from nested quotation
: nest2 |> x | [ 10 20 30 ] [: x + :] map ;
100 nest2 . cr

\ -- 13: |> across a shift/resume (frame relocation)
: worker2 |> x | shifter  x * ;
: ex2 reset 7 worker2 ;
ex2 3 swap resume . cr

\ -- 14: > marker on every local — same as |>
: all-recv | >a >b >c | a 100 *  b 10 *  c + + ;
1 2 3 all-recv . cr

\ -- 15: mixed — only middle local receives
: only-mid | x >y z | 7 to x  9 to z  x 1000 *  y 100 *  z 10 * + + ;
5 only-mid . cr

\ -- 16: mixed — first and last receive, middle local set later
: first-last | >a b >c | 4 to b  a 1000 *  b 100 *  c 10 * + + ;
2 8 first-last . cr

\ -- 17: mixed op inlined into caller body
: inlinee | x >y z | 10 to x  30 to z  x 100 *  y 10 *  z + + ;
inline
: outer-inline  77 inlinee ;
outer-inline . cr
